n### `App.tsx` â€” Root Component\n\n```tsx\nimport React from 'react';\nimport Home from './pages/Home';\n\nfunction App() {\n  return (\n    <div className=\"App\">\n      <h1>Welcome to React</h1>\n      <Home />\n    </div>\n  );\n}\n\nexport default App;\n```\n\n---\n\n## ğŸ§© 4. **Component Example**\n\n### `components/Button.tsx`\n\n```tsx\nimport React from 'react';\n\ntype Props = {\n  label: string;\n  onClick: () => void;\n};\n\nconst Button: React.FC<Props> = ({ label, onClick }) => (\n  <button onClick={onClick} className=\"btn\">\n    {label}\n  </button>\n);\n\nexport default Button;\n```\n\n---\n\n## ğŸŒ 5. **Routing Setup (with `react-router-dom`)**\n\n### ğŸ“¦ Install\n\n```bash\nnpm install react-router-dom\n```\n\n### ğŸ› ï¸ Setup\n\n#### `main.tsx`\n\n```tsx\nimport { BrowserRouter } from 'react-router-dom';\n\nReactDOM.createRoot(document.getElementById('root')!).render(\n  <BrowserRouter>\n    <App />\n  </BrowserRouter>\n);\n```\n\n#### `App.tsx`\n\n```tsx\nimport { Routes, Route } from 'react-router-dom';\nimport Home from './pages/Home';\nimport About from './pages/About';\n\nfunction App() {\n  return (\n    <Routes>\n      <Route path=\"/\" element={<Home />} />\n      <Route path=\"/about\" element={<About />} />\n    </Routes>\n  );\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## ğŸ£ 6. **Custom Hook Example**\n\n### `hooks/useCounter.ts`\n\n```tsx\nimport { useState } from 'react';\n\nexport function useCounter(initial = 0) {\n  const [count, setCount] = useState(initial);\n  const increment = () => setCount((c) => c + 1);\n  const decrement = () => setCount((c) => c - 1);\n  return { count, increment, decrement };\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## ğŸ§ª 7. **Testing Setup**\n\n### ğŸ“¦ Install\n\n```bash\nnpm install --save-dev vitest @testing-library/react @testing-library/jest-dom\n```\n\n### `Button.test.tsx`\n\n```tsx\nimport { render, screen } from '@testing-library/react';\nimport Button from './Button';\n\ntest('renders button with label', () => {\n  render(<Button label=\"Click me\" onClick={() => {}} />);\n  expect(screen.getByText('Click me')).toBeInTheDocument();\n});\n```\n\n---\n\n## ğŸ§¼ 8. **Linting + Formatting**\n\n### ğŸ“¦ Install\n\n```bash\nnpm install -D eslint prettier eslint-plugin-react eslint-config-prettier\n```\n\n### `.eslintrc.cjs`\n\n```js\nmodule.exports = {\n  extends: ['react-app', 'plugin:react/recommended', 'prettier'],\n};\n```\n\n---\n\n## ğŸ¨ 9. **Styling Options**\n\n| Approach          | Tools                           |\n| ----------------- | ------------------------------- |\n| Utility-first CSS | Tailwind CSS                    |\n| Component-scoped  | CSS Modules / Styled-components |\n| Global CSS        | Plain CSS / SCSS                |\n\n```bash\n# Tailwind example setup\nnpm install -D tailwindcss postcss autoprefixer\nnpx tailwindcss init -p\n```\n\n---\n\n## ğŸ“¦ 10. **Helpful Commands**\n\n| Task             | Command                        |\n| ---------------- | ------------------------------ |\n| Start dev server | `npm run dev`                  |\n| Build for prod   | `npm run build`                |\n| Preview build    | `npm run preview`              |\n| Run tests        | `npx vitest` or `npm run test` |\n| Format code      | `npx prettier --write .`       |\n\n---\n","srcMarkdownNoYaml":"\n\n\n\n<!-- WARNING: THIS FILE WAS AUTOGENERATED! DO NOT EDIT! -->\n\n---\n\n## ğŸš€ 1. **Quick Setup (Vite + React + TypeScript)**\n\n### ğŸ“¦ Installation\n\n```bash\n# Create project\nnpm create vite@latest my-app -- --template react-ts\n\n# Move into project\ncd my-app\n\n# Install dependencies\nnpm install\n\n# Start dev server\nnpm run dev\n```\n\n---\n\n## ğŸ—‚ï¸ 2. **Project Structure Explained**\n\n```\nmy-app/\nâ”œâ”€â”€ public/               # Static assets (favicon, robots.txt)\nâ”‚   â””â”€â”€ vite.svg\nâ”œâ”€â”€ src/                  # All source code lives here\nâ”‚   â”œâ”€â”€ assets/           # Images, fonts, etc.\nâ”‚   â”œâ”€â”€ components/       # Reusable UI component